        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "I merged several \"close to complete\" PRs and I think we're set for a first alpha release now. A fresh nightly wheel just went out this morning, so let's let that sink in for a moment, and then I'll prepare the release for PyPI.\n\nI'll leave a bit more time to the type constructor and initial assignment inference PRs (https://github.com/cython/cython/pull/7697 and https://github.com/cython/cython/pull/7686). They turned out to be less impactful than expected, so if we can get them in shape before a beta release, it'll be fine to bring them in, if we can't, then it won't hurt.\n\nMeanwhile, I'll prepare 3.2.6 to have both branches in a clean released state.",
